3
00:00:06.476 --> 00:00:09.729
in an effort to begin genuine global peace dialogue.

4
00:00:09.729 --> 00:00:11.425
With women at the table,

5
00:00:11.425 --> 00:00:14.443
healing and healthy compromise are possible.

6
00:00:14.443 --> 00:00:16.555
This is, in part, because the female brain

7
00:00:16.555 --> 00:00:18.336
is wired more for diplomacy

8
00:00:18.336 --> 00:00:21.195
and moving between creative and logical processes,

9
00:00:21.195 --> 00:00:23.541
which is required in finding solutions.

10
00:00:23.541 --> 00:00:25.092
As a professor of psychiatry

11
00:00:25.092 --> 00:00:27.342
at the University of San Francisco,

12
00:00:27.342 --> 00:00:30.382
her prestigious career as a feminine cultural leader

13
00:00:30.382 --> 00:00:32.398
has inspired many women to begin

14
00:00:32.398 --> 00:00:34.744
gathering in circles around the world,

15
00:00:34.744 --> 00:00:36.238
and to make their presence known

16
00:00:36.238 --> 00:00:38.157
in political arenas and board rooms

17
00:00:38.157 --> 00:00:40.579
to create a more compassionate and mature

18
00:00:40.579 --> 00:00:43.109
species through conscious parenting.

19
00:00:43.889 --> 00:00:47.828 line:15% 
(peaceful music)

20
00:00:48.164 --> 00:00:51.586
<v Voiceover>Let's go back in time into Grecian history</v>

21
00:00:51.586 --> 00:00:53.508
to something that we know, really,

22
00:00:53.508 --> 00:00:56.185
very little about called the Eleusinian Mystery.

23
00:00:56.185 --> 00:00:59.620
Having a background in mythology and psychology

24
00:00:59.620 --> 00:01:01.870
and understanding the roots of mythology

25
00:01:01.870 --> 00:01:03.886
and their affect on today's world,

26
00:01:03.886 --> 00:01:06.653
can you tell us a little bit about that?

27
00:01:06.979 --> 00:01:10.627
<v ->Imagine, for 2,500 years,</v>

28
00:01:11.677 --> 00:01:15.428
the mystery religion, from which the word mystic comes,

29
00:01:15.428 --> 00:01:20.072
was a trinity of the feminine,

30
00:01:20.327 --> 00:01:22.958
and it was the same story as the Easter story.

31
00:01:22.958 --> 00:01:26.296
That the divine daughter was abducted

32
00:01:26.296 --> 00:01:30.667
into the realm of death, and came back.

33
00:01:31.537 --> 00:01:36.390
The spiritual experience of the initiates

34
00:01:36.390 --> 00:01:38.993
was that they shared the journey of the divine daughter,

35
00:01:38.993 --> 00:01:41.958
and did not have to fear death.

36
00:01:41.958 --> 00:01:44.166
<v Voiceover>Interesting, this was personified</v>

37
00:01:44.166 --> 00:01:45.627
by Persephone, right?

38
00:01:45.627 --> 00:01:49.093
<v ->Right, Persephone, who returns in the spring, abducted;</v>

39
00:01:49.093 --> 00:01:52.667
it's that annual celebratory experience of

40
00:01:52.667 --> 00:01:55.056
winter followed by spring,

41
00:01:55.056 --> 00:01:59.631
and the whole pattern of the planet

42
00:01:59.631 --> 00:02:03.060
being something that we live out ourselves.

43
00:02:03.418 --> 00:02:06.202
So, there was an overlap between Christianity

44
00:02:06.202 --> 00:02:08.644
and the Eleusinian mysteries that,

45
00:02:08.644 --> 00:02:13.644
like, one or two of the church fathers were initiates

46
00:02:15.247 --> 00:02:17.774
because the Eleusinian mysteries did not end

47
00:02:17.774 --> 00:02:22.056
until it was destroyed by the Visigoth in 340 AD.

48
00:02:22.256 --> 00:02:27.256
So there was an overlap, and it was interesting that

49
00:02:27.619 --> 00:02:31.215
at a time when mythology was patriarchal,

50
00:02:31.215 --> 00:02:33.466
that is, Zeus ruled over everything,

51
00:02:33.466 --> 00:02:38.466
the spiritual experience of the Greek people involved

52
00:02:39.407 --> 00:02:44.407
the goddess of the grey and the great mother for Greece,

53
00:02:44.729 --> 00:02:47.769
which was Demeter,

54
00:02:47.769 --> 00:02:52.014
and her abducted daughter, Persephone.

55
00:02:52.014 --> 00:02:56.579
In the story, there's also a key figure called Hecate,

56
00:02:56.579 --> 00:03:00.429
so it was a trinity of maiden, mother, crone.

57
00:03:00.429 --> 00:03:02.914
<v Voiceover>Maiden, mother and crone.</v>

58
00:03:02.914 --> 00:03:05.378
So, that was the trinity prior to

59
00:03:05.378 --> 00:03:08.226
the introduction of Christianity.

60
00:03:08.226 --> 00:03:11.021
<v ->It absolutely was; there was a time when</v>

61
00:03:11.021 --> 00:03:15.127
people worshipped and revered the great goddess.

62
00:03:15.127 --> 00:03:17.495
<v Voiceover>For the life-giving properties,</v>

63
00:03:17.495 --> 00:03:19.820
obviously, and the cycle of renewal.

64
00:03:19.820 --> 00:03:22.395
<v ->Right, birth-giving, nurturing,</v>

65
00:03:23.175 --> 00:03:26.540
womb and tomb, actually, because we,

66
00:03:26.540 --> 00:03:28.140
everything emerges out of the earth,

67
00:03:28.140 --> 00:03:29.872
then goes back to earth.

68
00:03:29.872 --> 00:03:33.616
<v Voiceover>So, where have we come,</v>

69
00:03:33.616 --> 00:03:38.616
from the time when these mythological remembrances,

70
00:03:39.003 --> 00:03:43.760
passed down traditions had a very large impact on society,

71
00:03:43.760 --> 00:03:46.842
to, let's just jump forward a couple thousand years

72
00:03:46.842 --> 00:03:48.453
to where we are right now.

73
00:03:48.453 --> 00:03:50.564
We'll just kind of get to it.

74
00:03:50.564 --> 00:03:53.860
What has happened to us as a species by

75
00:03:53.860 --> 00:03:57.075
no longer having these same types

76
00:03:57.075 --> 00:03:59.940
of nurturing traditions, oral traditions?

77
00:03:59.940 --> 00:04:01.597
<v ->Well, we've completely lost balance</v>

78
00:04:01.597 --> 00:04:03.336
between masculine and feminine.

79
00:04:03.336 --> 00:04:06.194
The feminine, the divine feminine, the sacred feminine,

80
00:04:06.194 --> 00:04:11.194
the idea that women are carriers of divinity as well as men,

81
00:04:11.346 --> 00:04:14.450
got totally suppressed, and stories such as

82
00:04:14.450 --> 00:04:17.616
the grail that got hidden in the underworld,

83
00:04:17.616 --> 00:04:18.938
well, hidden in the forest,

84
00:04:18.938 --> 00:04:22.053
is a metaphor for the hidden feminine

85
00:04:22.053 --> 00:04:24.495
that could heal the patriarchy,

86
00:04:24.495 --> 00:04:26.234
which is a wounded future king.

87
00:04:26.234 --> 00:04:28.497
So, we've arrived at a time in history

88
00:04:28.497 --> 00:04:32.292
where there could be a turning point.

89
00:04:32.292 --> 00:04:34.521
If we continue in the direction we're going,

90
00:04:34.521 --> 00:04:36.398
we will use up the planet,

91
00:04:36.398 --> 00:04:40.821
and the opportunity to evolve and to become

92
00:04:41.551 --> 00:04:46.008
who we are actually capable of becoming as human beings

93
00:04:46.008 --> 00:04:47.608
will be lost.

94
00:04:47.608 --> 00:04:50.371
I think we have, maybe only a window of opportunity

95
00:04:50.371 --> 00:04:53.763
of several decades in which the feminine

96
00:04:53.763 --> 00:04:57.607
could actually come into the world and make a difference.

97
00:04:57.978 --> 00:05:00.506
The reason I say that is because

98
00:05:00.506 --> 00:05:02.554
there is a generation of women

99
00:05:02.554 --> 00:05:05.221
that has never existed before on this planet.

100
00:05:05.221 --> 00:05:07.236
<v Voiceover>Could you elaborate on that?</v>

101
00:05:07.236 --> 00:05:10.543
<v ->Well, ever since the late '60's and '70's,</v>

102
00:05:10.543 --> 00:05:14.809
we've had, first of all, in numbers in the United States,

103
00:05:14.809 --> 00:05:17.039
it's a baby boomer generation.

104
00:05:17.039 --> 00:05:20.132
So, at this present time, women over 50,

105
00:05:20.132 --> 00:05:23.054
who have been educated, who have had

106
00:05:23.054 --> 00:05:25.283
positions of responsibility, who've had choices

107
00:05:25.283 --> 00:05:28.323
about birth control, who have chosen

108
00:05:28.323 --> 00:05:30.552
what spiritual traditions they might follow,

109
00:05:30.552 --> 00:05:34.520
and who have networked, loved, cared for each other,

110
00:05:34.520 --> 00:05:37.059
and for the first time, had a sense

111
00:05:37.059 --> 00:05:39.426
that to be a woman is a good thing.

112
00:05:39.426 --> 00:05:42.797
Here we are with all the fundamentalists

113
00:05:42.797 --> 00:05:47.202
of the patriarchal religions wanting us to go back to--

114
00:05:47.202 --> 00:05:49.133
<v Voiceover>Barefoot and pregnant.</v>

115
00:05:49.133 --> 00:05:51.362
<v ->Or burka-ized, or something like that.</v>

116
00:05:51.362 --> 00:05:52.524
(laughter)

117
00:05:52.524 --> 00:05:55.095
So, the influence that we can have

118
00:05:55.095 --> 00:05:58.977
will exist only for the next couple of decades.

119
00:05:58.977 --> 00:06:02.806
And, I'm personally feeling

120
00:06:02.806 --> 00:06:06.358
myself and others as being, sort of message carriers.

121
00:06:06.358 --> 00:06:09.963
Urgent Message From Mother is talking about

122
00:06:09.963 --> 00:06:12.907
mother earth, the maternal instinct, the sacred feminine,

123
00:06:12.907 --> 00:06:16.693
that is recognizing that it is women

124
00:06:16.693 --> 00:06:18.944
that could make a difference and change the world.

125
00:06:18.944 --> 00:06:21.706
That it's not up to the men, but it's up to women

126
00:06:21.706 --> 00:06:24.917
to bring the feminine principle into balance.

127
00:06:24.917 --> 00:06:27.462
<v Voiceover>And yet, there is so much</v>

128
00:06:27.462 --> 00:06:31.216
conflicting pressure on society.

129
00:06:31.216 --> 00:06:33.616
Some things that just pop to mind,

130
00:06:33.616 --> 00:06:36.240
and I know this could become tangential here,

131
00:06:36.240 --> 00:06:37.371
but that's okay,

132
00:06:37.371 --> 00:06:41.648
is that women now, as a result of some of,

133
00:06:41.648 --> 00:06:44.154
as you say, the freedoms and educations and such

134
00:06:44.154 --> 00:06:45.573
that we have now,

135
00:06:45.573 --> 00:06:47.407
there's another thing running along side it,

136
00:06:47.407 --> 00:06:51.471
i.e. Lara Croft, and that is that women are now

