00:07:05.817 --> 00:07:10.817
trying to be some ideal that doesn't exist in nature.

144
00:07:11.064 --> 00:07:12.366
(laughter)

145
00:07:12.366 --> 00:07:15.363
And so then you have the self-loathing of women

146
00:07:15.363 --> 00:07:18.211
that go along with that: body imagery, all these

147
00:07:18.211 --> 00:07:21.027
conflicting things happening at this incredible time,

148
00:07:21.027 --> 00:07:23.554
can you just comment on all this a bit?

149
00:07:23.554 --> 00:07:27.362
<v ->Well, there's always been a layer of self-loathing</v>

150
00:07:27.362 --> 00:07:32.362
because to be a woman is to be an inferior human being

151
00:07:32.567 --> 00:07:35.788
in the way of old tradition.

152
00:07:35.788 --> 00:07:39.457
So, that's, the form it takes may be different now,

153
00:07:39.457 --> 00:07:43.596
but the sort of depreciation of one's own gender

154
00:07:43.596 --> 00:07:48.097
has been ever since patriarchy, basically.

155
00:07:50.537 --> 00:07:53.441
When women were not allowed to be educated,

156
00:07:53.441 --> 00:07:55.883
didn't vote, didn't do a number of things,

157
00:07:55.883 --> 00:07:58.571
they, obviously, appeared to be inferior.

158
00:07:58.571 --> 00:08:03.571
So, the inferior, feeling inferior is nothing new.

159
00:08:03.783 --> 00:08:06.823
Now, what is new is that the emergence,

160
00:08:06.823 --> 00:08:09.586
one, of women with a sister archetype,

161
00:08:09.586 --> 00:08:11.761
the bonding, the feminist movement.

162
00:08:11.761 --> 00:08:16.188
The sense of the positive element of the maternal

163
00:08:17.398 --> 00:08:21.223
so that what we have now

164
00:08:21.223 --> 00:08:23.964
is not all women or all men,

165
00:08:23.964 --> 00:08:26.844
we're, there's an individuality among the gender,

166
00:08:26.844 --> 00:08:30.076
for one thing, so that, though I'm talking about

167
00:08:30.076 --> 00:08:33.393
it's up to women, it's up to men and women

168
00:08:33.393 --> 00:08:36.742
that have a bond to the feminine principle,

169
00:08:36.742 --> 00:08:40.667
and therefore feel an interdependency of life,

170
00:08:40.667 --> 00:08:43.441
and a realization that unless we

171
00:08:43.441 --> 00:08:45.499
tap into that interdependency and look out

172
00:08:45.499 --> 00:08:48.240
for the planet, for each other,

173
00:08:48.240 --> 00:08:52.357
that the inevitable war that will be a

174
00:08:52.357 --> 00:08:55.536
nuclear winter disaster, or we'll just use up the planet,

175
00:08:55.536 --> 00:08:59.045
and with nuclear warming and with overpopulation,

176
00:08:59.045 --> 00:09:02.170
we'll just do in our resources, so there's all of that

177
00:09:02.170 --> 00:09:06.469
going on, clearly, that we are at a time when

178
00:09:06.469 --> 00:09:09.092
the tipping point experience could happen.

179
00:09:09.092 --> 00:09:13.369
Now, because you and I have been through

180
00:09:13.369 --> 00:09:15.065
the women's movement experience

181
00:09:15.065 --> 00:09:16.665
and seen the influence,

182
00:09:16.665 --> 00:09:18.756
well, it was just women meeting together

183
00:09:18.756 --> 00:09:20.889
in small consciousness raising groups.

184
00:09:20.889 --> 00:09:23.929
It wasn't a orchestrated from the tops thing at all.

185
00:09:23.929 --> 00:09:27.043
It had to do with tapping into,

186
00:09:27.043 --> 00:09:29.294
we can either call it the morphic field phenomenon,

187
00:09:29.294 --> 00:09:33.773
or we can look at Malcolm Gladwell and look at tipping point

188
00:09:33.773 --> 00:09:36.397
but when a critical mass of people change

189
00:09:36.397 --> 00:09:38.563
how they think, how they feel,

190
00:09:38.563 --> 00:09:42.178
what was either repressed or unthinkable

191
00:09:42.178 --> 00:09:45.293
or condemned from the pulpit becomes the new norm.

192
00:09:45.293 --> 00:09:48.845
And that happens amazingly rapidly

193
00:09:48.845 --> 00:09:50.860
when the tipping point occurs.

194
00:09:50.860 --> 00:09:51.863
There was that saying,

195
00:09:51.863 --> 00:09:53.516
"There's nothing so powerful as an idea

196
00:09:53.516 --> 00:09:54.807
"whose time has come."

197
00:09:54.807 --> 00:09:56.204
<v Jean>It's true.</v>
<v Voiceover>Has it come?</v>

198
00:09:56.204 --> 00:09:58.359
<v ->Not yet, but it's moving.</v>

199
00:09:58.359 --> 00:09:59.843
<v Voiceover>I'm not seeing it because the women</v>

200
00:09:59.843 --> 00:10:02.041
in Congress are acting a lot like the men in a lot of cases.

201
00:10:02.041 --> 00:10:03.182
<v ->Well, they have to.</v>

202
00:10:03.182 --> 00:10:04.270
<v Voiceover>That's true.</v>
<v Jean>Up until,</v>

203
00:10:04.270 --> 00:10:06.873
they have to until there is a critical number,

204
00:10:06.873 --> 00:10:11.011
and the United Nations number would be

205
00:10:11.011 --> 00:10:13.539
that you have to have at least 30% of the Parliament

206
00:10:13.539 --> 00:10:18.531
women before women start to voice and stand for,

207
00:10:18.531 --> 00:10:23.218
like, education and maternal care and things like that.

208
00:10:23.701 --> 00:10:25.808
Up until that point, women have to

209
00:10:25.808 --> 00:10:28.485
look and be on the committees that have power,

210
00:10:28.485 --> 00:10:30.991
so they're, in order to be respected.

211
00:10:30.991 --> 00:10:32.357
<v Voiceover>They have to play ball just to be there.</v>

212
00:10:32.357 --> 00:10:34.884
<v ->Right, so we have something,</v>

213
00:10:34.884 --> 00:10:39.475
as I recall, we have something like 14% of our Congress,

214
00:10:39.475 --> 00:10:43.123
Senators and House, women.

215
00:10:43.123 --> 00:10:45.896
There are at least 16 countries where women

216
00:10:45.896 --> 00:10:49.885
do have over 30%, and one of the,

217
00:10:49.885 --> 00:10:52.392
the one that has more than any other

218
00:10:52.392 --> 00:10:55.698
<v Jean>is Rwanda.</v>
<v Voiceover>Interesting.</v>

219
00:10:55.698 --> 00:11:00.033
<v ->43% women, and it's women together.</v>

220
00:11:00.295 --> 00:11:03.985
Now, after 800,000 people were massacred

221
00:11:03.985 --> 00:11:06.524
in a short period of time,

222
00:11:06.524 --> 00:11:10.662
and there were orphanages just filled with children,

223
00:11:10.662 --> 00:11:12.656
it was women getting together,

224
00:11:12.656 --> 00:11:14.777
reconciling with the situation,

225
00:11:14.777 --> 00:11:17.433
and deciding out of their maternal instinct

226
00:11:17.433 --> 00:11:21.433
that they needed to adopt with no consideration

227
00:11:21.433 --> 00:11:24.003
whether they were Tutsi children or Hutu children.

228
00:11:24.003 --> 00:11:25.240
<v Voiceover>That's so beautiful.</v>

229
00:11:25.240 --> 00:11:29.368
<v ->And so, it had to do with what women,</v>

230
00:11:29.368 --> 00:11:32.035
as a gender have physiologically,

231
00:11:32.035 --> 00:11:36.024
and that is, one, an ability to

232
00:11:37.705 --> 00:11:41.139
physiologically be the more empathic gender,

233
00:11:41.139 --> 00:11:45.363
has to do with how, when stress occurs,

234
00:11:45.363 --> 00:11:48.915
men, as a gender, go to flight or fight,

235
00:11:48.915 --> 00:11:50.846
and ever since the research that was done

236
00:11:50.846 --> 00:11:55.272
at UCLA in 1991, we know that women tend,

237
00:11:55.272 --> 00:11:58.898
when stressed, to want to talk to the other women

238
00:11:58.898 --> 00:12:01.682
closest to them, and that when they do,

239
00:12:01.682 --> 00:12:03.335
the stress level goes down,

240
00:12:03.335 --> 00:12:05.351
and the maternal bonding hormone,

241
00:12:05.351 --> 00:12:07.538
called Oxytocin, goes up.

242
00:12:07.538 --> 00:12:11.015
So essentially, if there's ever to be peace

243
00:12:11.015 --> 00:12:12.647
negotiated well in this world,

244
00:12:12.647 --> 00:12:14.737
women have to be at the table.

245
00:12:14.737 --> 00:12:17.244
And the United Nations has recognized it.

246
00:12:17.244 --> 00:12:22.244
That with UN resolution 1325, which is referred to as,

247
00:12:23.654 --> 00:12:26.022
"the women, peace and security resolution."

248
00:12:26.022 --> 00:12:29.435
It says wherever conflict is in the works,

249
00:12:29.435 --> 00:12:33.008
or happening or after, women need to be involved,

250
00:12:33.008 --> 00:12:36.859
and we don't impose it on the major conflicts.

251
00:12:36.859 --> 00:12:39.418
I mean, you look at the Middle East,

252
00:12:39.418 --> 00:12:42.522
you don't see women involved in the peace process.

253
00:12:42.522 --> 00:12:45.381
But, when it's imposed, it's interesting,

254
00:12:45.381 --> 00:12:47.493
because it was imposed on Sierra Leone,

255
00:12:47.493 --> 00:12:51.460
and I was at the commission on the status of women

256
