00:28:05.354 --> 00:28:09.205
that just before things change, there is a real repression.

565
00:28:09.205 --> 00:28:11.338
It's like hand wrestling, you know.

566
00:28:11.338 --> 00:28:15.754
It's like this, and then there's a real push,

567
00:28:15.754 --> 00:28:17.823
and then it tips, and when it tips,

568
00:28:17.823 --> 00:28:20.329
it's like there's a new era.

569
00:28:20.329 --> 00:28:25.044
That we go from the age of faith,

570
00:28:25.044 --> 00:28:27.828
as it got more and more corrupted, into the Reformation,

571
00:28:27.828 --> 00:28:31.678
or we went from the Medieval Times to the Renaissance.

572
00:28:31.678 --> 00:28:33.982
There's a point in which

573
00:28:33.982 --> 00:28:36.136
something is rising up to the grassroots,

574
00:28:36.136 --> 00:28:38.227
and then it tips.

575
00:28:38.227 --> 00:28:39.848
<v Voiceover>Where are we in that continuum,</v>

576
00:28:39.848 --> 00:28:41.661
because it seems like we're experiencing

577
00:28:41.661 --> 00:28:45.469
a bit of the repression right now, attempted repression?

578
00:28:45.469 --> 00:28:47.912
<v ->Well, the fundamentalists of all of the major religions</v>

579
00:28:47.912 --> 00:28:51.442
have the apparent upper hand,

580
00:28:51.442 --> 00:28:56.442
but there's an awful lot of energy in the others

581
00:28:57.479 --> 00:29:01.095
who are saying, "Wait a minute, this was not the message

582
00:29:01.095 --> 00:29:03.953
"of our religion."

583
00:29:03.953 --> 00:29:08.953
And, the grassroots are usually quite quiet

584
00:29:09.500 --> 00:29:13.819
until there reaches a point where something shifts it.

585
00:29:13.819 --> 00:29:15.355
<v Voiceover>How do you perceive</v>

586
00:29:15.355 --> 00:29:16.891
that shifting point right now,

587
00:29:16.891 --> 00:29:19.739
with the apparent repression on one hand,

588
00:29:19.739 --> 00:29:23.088
and yet, the quiet masses that are not sleeping,

589
00:29:23.088 --> 00:29:24.528
that are waking up?

590
00:29:24.528 --> 00:29:27.077
<v ->Because I'm one of the message carriers,</v>

591
00:29:27.077 --> 00:29:30.725
and when I articulate that it's up to women

592
00:29:30.725 --> 00:29:34.373
in great numbers, and we're 52% of the world's population,

593
00:29:36.023 --> 00:29:39.294
and I get a sense that I'm putting words

594
00:29:39.294 --> 00:29:42.077
to the feeling that is emerging in the psyche of people,

595
00:29:42.077 --> 00:29:45.213
I get a feeling that the morphic field is active,

596
00:29:45.213 --> 00:29:47.645
and that very close to the surface,

597
00:29:47.645 --> 00:29:49.896
coming at individuals, because that's how it works.

598
00:29:49.896 --> 00:29:51.965
You think you have an original idea,

599
00:29:51.965 --> 00:29:54.610
but, and it is original to you,

600
00:29:54.610 --> 00:29:56.797
but it so happens that the collective psyche

601
00:29:56.797 --> 00:30:00.882
is rising with the same idea,

602
00:30:00.882 --> 00:30:04.039
and so, you give it, I give it a different form

603
00:30:04.039 --> 00:30:05.948
that's uniquely our own form,

604
00:30:05.948 --> 00:30:08.966
and it comes to us as an original idea.

605
00:30:08.966 --> 00:30:10.513
But then, we look around and we say,

606
00:30:10.513 --> 00:30:12.241
<v Voiceover>It's everywhere!</v>

607
00:30:12.241 --> 00:30:14.001
<v ->It is really coming up everywhere!</v>

608
00:30:14.001 --> 00:30:15.419
<v Voiceover>Very true, and there have been</v>

609
00:30:15.419 --> 00:30:17.734
clinical experiments proving the power of the masses,

610
00:30:17.734 --> 00:30:20.118
and the correctness of decisions that are made

611
00:30:20.118 --> 00:30:22.603
when it genuinely comes from the mass consciousness.

612
00:30:22.603 --> 00:30:24.043
So you're seeing that we are

613
00:30:24.043 --> 00:30:26.347
getting toward that tipping point?

614
00:30:26.347 --> 00:30:27.989
<v ->I'm thinking we are.</v>

615
00:30:27.989 --> 00:30:31.594
<v Voiceover>Just give us, in your opinion,</v>

616
00:30:31.594 --> 00:30:34.559
a few things that need to be done now;

617
00:30:34.559 --> 00:30:37.493
the sense of the urgent message from mother earth,

618
00:30:37.493 --> 00:30:41.066
that need to happen now among people of the planet,

619
00:30:41.066 --> 00:30:44.042
women and men, in order to facilitate

620
00:30:44.042 --> 00:30:47.561
this tipping point and this, hopefully, saving grace.

621
00:30:47.561 --> 00:30:50.836
<v ->Well, first of all, one of the things</v>

622
00:30:50.836 --> 00:30:54.462
that could really help it to move even faster

623
00:30:54.462 --> 00:30:58.878
is if there would be a fifth United Nations

624
00:30:58.878 --> 00:31:00.872
Women World conference.

625
00:31:00.872 --> 00:31:03.656
The last one was in Beijing in 1995.

626
00:31:03.656 --> 00:31:06.045
There were 50,000 people who went to this

627
00:31:06.045 --> 00:31:08.552
conference in Beijing.

628
00:31:08.552 --> 00:31:10.248
It was hard to get to and all of that,

629
00:31:10.248 --> 00:31:12.808
and out of it came a document called,

630
00:31:12.808 --> 00:31:14.269
"the platform for action,"

631
00:31:14.269 --> 00:31:19.015
which, if implemented, would bring women and men

632
00:31:19.015 --> 00:31:22.034
into a balanced kind of conscious society

633
00:31:22.034 --> 00:31:25.948
in that it would raise and overcome

634
00:31:25.948 --> 00:31:29.617
the oppression that women, globally, are experiencing.

635
00:31:29.617 --> 00:31:33.062
So, we thought back in those days

636
00:31:33.062 --> 00:31:35.388
that since there had been four in a row,

637
00:31:35.388 --> 00:31:38.097
that by 2005--

638
00:31:38.097 --> 00:31:40.305
<v Voiceover>Might have been another one.</v>

639
00:31:40.305 --> 00:31:41.137
(laughter)

640
00:31:41.137 --> 00:31:42.907
<v ->And then, for me to find out with others</v>

641
00:31:42.907 --> 00:31:45.926
that it's not happening; it's not gonna happen

642
00:31:45.926 --> 00:31:48.315
unless there's enough grassroots energy

643
00:31:48.315 --> 00:31:50.821
to influence our respective countries,

644
00:31:50.821 --> 00:31:53.125
and to influence the United Nations to have one,

645
00:31:53.125 --> 00:31:57.349
and it would be the first one since the internet and emails.

646
00:31:57.349 --> 00:32:01.338
Can you imagine how it could be to have 300,000 women--

647
00:32:01.338 --> 00:32:02.597
<v Voiceover>That could gain some traction.</v>

648
00:32:02.597 --> 00:32:05.732
<v ->Coming to a conference in a place like Canada for example?</v>

649
00:32:05.732 --> 00:32:07.450
Which happens to be a place that I'm

650
00:32:07.450 --> 00:32:10.441
energizingly trying to involve.

651
00:32:12.115 --> 00:32:17.115
To have those websites up and emails going beforehand,

652
00:32:18.841 --> 00:32:21.369
meeting, getting inspired, learning from each other

653
00:32:21.369 --> 00:32:22.904
what's possible, who does what,

654
00:32:22.904 --> 00:32:24.344
because basically, it's always,

655
00:32:24.344 --> 00:32:27.619
"Well, if he or she could do that, I could do that, too."

656
00:32:27.619 --> 00:32:29.304
You know, this is possible.

657
00:32:29.304 --> 00:32:32.440
And then, you get mentors and you get inspired,

658
00:32:32.440 --> 00:32:35.181
and then you get follow-ups afterwards with emails.

659
00:32:35.181 --> 00:32:38.082
Can you imagine how fast something would move?

660
00:32:38.082 --> 00:32:40.941
So I'm out there thinking that this is something

661
00:32:42.881 --> 00:32:44.684
that needs to be done.

662
00:32:44.684 --> 00:32:49.122
And I'm thinking that that would be easy enough,

663
00:32:49.122 --> 00:32:51.031
that shouldn't take too much.

664
00:32:51.031 --> 00:32:54.273
You can go on the internet and download a petition

665
00:32:54.273 --> 00:32:59.273
on www, 5wwc.org, for example.

666
00:33:02.177 --> 00:33:05.945
And then, there are all of the connections

667
00:33:05.945 --> 00:33:08.260
that are happening between and among circles.

668
00:33:08.260 --> 00:33:13.260
On the interface side, there's United Religious Initiative,

669
00:33:13.582 --> 00:33:18.200
there's The Millionth Circle, there's GatherTheWomen.org.

670
00:33:19.610 --> 00:33:23.320
Again, this is speaking to there is something rising

671
00:33:23.320 --> 00:33:27.821
in that direction, so I think that is a very good sign.

672
00:33:27.821 --> 00:33:31.789
I think that, hopefully, the elections in the next

673
00:33:31.789 --> 00:33:36.789
congressional elections will show that the American people

674
00:33:36.834 --> 00:33:40.311
are no longer going along with war as an answer.

675
00:33:40.311 --> 00:33:41.964
<v Jean>We'll see.</v>
<v Voiceover>Let's hope.</v>

676
00:33:41.964 --> 00:33:43.628
<v ->Let's hope, let's see.</v>

677
00:33:43.628 --> 00:33:46.902
And then, the signs, because right now,

678
00:33:46.902 --> 00:33:51.457
it's more like an intuitive read of what is happening.

679
00:33:51.457 --> 00:33:53.366
<v Voiceover>But you have your ear to the ground,</v>

680
00:33:53.366 --> 00:33:54.731
you're out there.

681
00:33:54.731 --> 00:33:56.960
<v ->And it feels good.</v>

682
00:33:56.960 --> 00:34:01.952
I'm also trying to recruit people, but women especially,

683
00:34:01.952 --> 00:34:06.389
and people in their retirement age, we retire earlier.

684
00:34:06.389 --> 00:34:11.389
At 55, well, you might have 40 good years left!

685
00:34:11.616 --> 00:34:13.258
What are you going to do after, you know,

686
00:34:13.258 --> 00:34:15.509
you've already done the traveling to this or that,

687
00:34:15.509 --> 00:34:18.484
and you've meditated long enough.

688
00:34:18.484 --> 00:34:21.919
How about doing something to make a difference now

689
00:34:21.919 --> 00:34:24.617
because it's meaningful and fun?

690
00:34:24.617 --> 00:34:29.044
I have been exporting an idea that really has been

691
00:34:29.044 --> 00:34:33.022
my own notion about what keeps me moving,

692
00:34:33.022 --> 00:34:35.219
because I'm invited to do a number of things,

693
00:34:35.219 --> 00:34:38.174
and how do I decide?

694
00:34:38.174 --> 00:34:42.675
I started to think, well, one, I obviously have to be

695
00:34:42.675 --> 00:34:47.187
open to having the energy to do a next thing,

696
00:34:47.187 --> 00:34:51.709
but given that, I have three criteria.

697
00:34:51.709 --> 00:34:54.493
One is, is it meaningful?

698
00:34:54.493 --> 00:34:58.098
Well, a great many things that we are offered

699
00:34:58.098 --> 00:35:00.583
as possibilities fit that description.

700
00:35:00.583 --> 00:35:02.759
The second is, is it fun?

701
00:35:02.759 --> 00:35:04.924
And fun has to do with the people

702
00:35:04.924 --> 00:35:08.241
that do this thing that you might join.

703
00:35:08.241 --> 00:35:12.348
People that you can laugh with,

704
00:35:12.348 --> 00:35:14.257
people that you can be honest with,

705
00:35:14.257 --> 00:35:17.691
people that it feels like together you do more

706
00:35:17.691 --> 00:35:20.038
than if you did by yourself.

707
00:35:20.038 --> 00:35:23.056
The third criteria has to do with,

708
00:35:23.056 --> 00:35:26.608
is this whole undertaking motivated by love?

709
00:35:26.608 --> 00:35:29.296
It includes outraged love,

710
00:35:29.296 --> 00:35:31.781
because you can be outraged becuase you love the planet,

711
00:35:31.781 --> 00:35:33.598
or you love children, or you love trees,

712
00:35:33.598 --> 00:35:36.105
and you're watching what's being done

713
00:35:36.105 --> 00:35:39.827
and though there is an outraged energy,

714
00:35:39.827 --> 00:35:41.470
it's not done out of hate, it's out of--

715
00:35:41.470 --> 00:35:42.776
<v Voiceover>Passion.</v>

716
00:35:42.776 --> 00:35:45.075
<v ->It's out of the love for whatever it is</v>

717
00:35:45.075 --> 00:35:47.048
that you want to save.

718
00:35:47.048 --> 00:35:48.093
<v Voiceover>Right.</v>

719
00:35:48.093 --> 00:35:53.085
<v ->I think if people would take these three criteria to heart</v>

720
00:35:53.085 --> 00:35:57.981
with the notion that, if you're still here,

721
00:35:57.981 --> 00:36:01.554
life has prepared you, with all your resources

722
00:36:01.554 --> 00:36:05.244
and your intelligence and the ability to look at your life

723
00:36:05.244 --> 00:36:10.244
and say, "Compared to 95% of people on this planet,

724
00:36:10.364 --> 00:36:13.873
"I've really been given a lot.

725
00:36:13.873 --> 00:36:17.052
"Might it now be time to give back?"

726
00:36:17.052 --> 00:36:20.859
When you start giving back, it's a great energy!

727
00:36:20.859 --> 00:36:23.718
There's something that has come out, for example,

728
00:36:23.718 --> 00:36:26.320
with the people who go into long term remissions

729
00:36:26.320 --> 00:36:28.080
with cancer that could have killed them,

730
00:36:28.080 --> 00:36:30.128
or should have killed them, statistically,

731
00:36:30.128 --> 00:36:35.128
and invariably, part of what they're doing is altruistic.

732
00:36:35.749 --> 00:36:38.373
It is in some way giving back.

733
00:36:38.373 --> 00:36:41.061
It is being an activist in some personal way,

734
00:36:41.061 --> 00:36:43.567
in which they're getting a lot of juice

735
00:36:43.567 --> 00:36:45.679
out of helping some other people.

736
00:36:45.679 --> 00:36:47.930
<v Voiceover>Dr. Lorraine Day, who we also interviewed,</v>

737
00:36:47.930 --> 00:36:49.903
said that's a really critical part in healing.

738
00:36:49.903 --> 00:36:51.535
<v ->I'm sure it is.</v>

739
00:36:51.535 --> 00:36:54.361
Again, it's meaningful,

740
00:36:54.361 --> 00:36:55.876
(laughter)

741
00:36:55.876 --> 00:36:57.337
<v ->[Voiceover and Jean] Meaningful, fun,</v>

742
00:36:57.337 --> 00:36:58.756
and motivated by love.

743
00:36:58.756 --> 00:37:01.166
<v Voiceover>That sounds like a perfect criteria</v>

744
00:37:01.166 --> 00:37:02.766
for almost anything we do in life,

745
00:37:02.766 --> 00:37:06.318
and certainly helping the earth recover itself

746
00:37:06.318 --> 00:37:08.110
has got to be the best--

747
00:37:08.110 --> 00:37:10.414
<v ->Well see, the other thing is that only you can say</v>

748
00:37:10.414 --> 00:37:12.451
what these three things are.

749
00:37:12.451 --> 00:37:14.755
It's not other people saying it's meaningful.

750
00:37:14.755 --> 00:37:17.378
You're saying, "This is meaningful to me."

751
00:37:17.378 --> 00:37:22.274
Nobody can define who and what you do

752
00:37:22.274 --> 00:37:24.973
being fun, except yourself.

753
00:37:24.973 --> 00:37:29.282
And, whether or not you're motivated to do something

754
00:37:29.282 --> 00:37:31.906
because you love what you're doing or helping,

755
00:37:31.906 --> 00:37:36.906
again, it's all part of the authentic being that you are,

756
00:37:36.951 --> 00:37:39.041
and this is where I bring in

757
00:37:39.041 --> 00:37:41.782
the second half of life work as a Jungian analyst,

758
00:37:41.782 --> 00:37:44.897
is it's, Jung called it individuation.

759
00:37:44.897 --> 00:37:49.897
But it has to do with being the person that you could be

760
00:37:50.283 --> 00:37:52.790
based on the difficulties and the talents

761
00:37:52.790 --> 00:37:54.997
that you have gone through in the first half of life,

762
00:37:54.997 --> 00:37:56.523
the lessons you've learned,

763
00:37:56.523 --> 00:38:00.352
and now it's time to really have an individual life.

764
00:38:00.352 --> 00:38:04.469
We try to meet the expectations of family and culture

765
00:38:04.469 --> 00:38:05.973
in the first half of life.

766
00:38:05.973 --> 00:38:08.714
It has to do, usually, with relationship and career,

767
00:38:08.714 --> 00:38:12.628
and we either succeed or we don't to meet the

768
00:38:12.628 --> 00:38:16.756
general sense of this is what a competent adult manages.

769
00:38:16.756 --> 00:38:18.388
Then what?

770
00:38:18.388 --> 00:38:22.142
The next part of life is about us individually,

771
00:38:22.142 --> 00:38:24.137
what we came to do.

772
00:38:24.137 --> 00:38:28.233
I have thought so often about how everybody says

773
00:38:28.233 --> 00:38:30.803
and feels that they have a soul.

774
00:38:30.803 --> 00:38:33.128
Well, it's very curious, then.

775
00:38:33.128 --> 00:38:35.635
Because if we all have a sense of having a soul,

776
00:38:35.635 --> 00:38:40.115
then we're spiritual beings who've come into this

777
00:38:40.115 --> 00:38:43.250
strange experience called human life.

778
00:38:43.250 --> 00:38:44.573
(laughter)

779
00:38:44.573 --> 00:38:49.245
So, to reframe it, we're spiritual beings on a human path,

780
00:38:49.245 --> 00:38:50.845
rather than human beings who may

781
00:38:50.845 --> 00:38:53.564
or may not be on a spiritual path, okay?

782
00:38:53.564 --> 00:38:58.564
Then, there is, well, there must be something

783
00:38:58.951 --> 00:39:03.951
about an immortal soul that in this human experience

784
00:39:05.169 --> 00:39:09.809
can grow or not, or experience things or not,

785
00:39:09.809 --> 00:39:13.355
that even an immortal soul does not.

786
00:39:13.969 --> 00:39:16.315
I think it's about vulnerability and love,

787
00:39:16.315 --> 00:39:18.288
and it's about choices we make.

788
00:39:20.998 --> 00:39:24.069
Only we can determine such things as,

789
00:39:24.069 --> 00:39:27.791
and often, only as we're living life,

790
00:39:27.791 --> 00:39:29.668
what did we really come to do?

791
00:39:29.668 --> 00:39:30.895
<v Voiceover>The big question,</v>

792
00:39:30.895 --> 00:39:33.199
it's a question in many of us, now.

793
00:39:33.199 --> 00:39:35.865
<v ->Who did we really, or what did we really come to love?</v>

794
00:39:35.865 --> 00:39:37.838
And what are we here for?

795
00:39:40.718 --> 00:39:43.481
When you're doing something with your life

796
00:39:43.481 --> 00:39:48.481
that feels real and is using your life,

797
00:39:49.262 --> 00:39:51.544
what you knew through your suffering,

798
00:39:51.544 --> 00:39:53.379
and what you knew through your talents,

799
00:39:53.379 --> 00:39:57.112
your whole self is present, doing what you're doing,

800
00:39:57.112 --> 00:39:59.202
and it is quite delicious.

801
00:39:59.202 --> 00:40:04.202
I really think that, instead of so many of the things

802
00:40:04.567 --> 00:40:07.565
that people think is going to make them happy

803
00:40:07.565 --> 00:40:10.135
when they retire, that everybody should do that

804
00:40:10.135 --> 00:40:13.186
for a little while, but then they should heed a call

805
00:40:13.186 --> 00:40:14.988
to really make a difference.

806
00:40:14.988 --> 00:40:19.585
Because I think that if we're here and of this generation

807
00:40:19.585 --> 00:40:21.729
that could make a difference to this planet,

808
00:40:21.729 --> 00:40:25.275
that there's a purpose that we happen to be here right now.

809
00:40:25.718 --> 00:40:29.538 line:15% 
(peaceful music)

810
00:40:29.538 --> 00:40:32.983 line:15% 
<v ->I didn't even really know what a women's circle was.</v>

811
00:40:32.983 --> 00:40:35.116
I just knew I wanted to bring women together,

812
00:40:35.116 --> 00:40:37.495
and if we did it in the container of a circle,

813
00:40:37.495 --> 00:40:41.441
that somehow, it would be a magical formula,

814
00:40:41.441 --> 00:40:43.905
and indeed, it did serve to be so.

815
00:40:43.905 --> 00:40:45.462
A lot of the women in that first circle

816
00:40:45.462 --> 00:40:48.108
set their intention for their dream lives,

817
00:40:48.108 --> 00:40:50.454
and the things that have unfolded.

818
00:40:50.454 --> 00:40:51.798
It was amazing.

819
00:40:51.798 --> 00:40:53.771
Soon after I did that first circle,

820
00:40:53.771 --> 00:40:56.118
all of a sudden, people started giving me these books

821
00:40:56.118 --> 00:40:58.027
that were about creating women's circles,

822
00:40:58.027 --> 00:40:59.467
and The Millionth Circle,

823
00:40:59.467 --> 00:41:03.531
and creating women's spirituality circles,

824
00:41:03.531 --> 00:41:06.154
and all of these books, and I looked to see

825
00:41:06.154 --> 00:41:07.594
when they were published,

826
00:41:07.594 --> 00:41:10.464
and it was the same year that I got the nudge

827
00:41:10.464 --> 00:41:12.447
to start my own women's circle.

828
00:41:12.447 --> 00:41:14.346
It was at that time I realized,

829
00:41:14.346 --> 00:41:16.202
"Oh my god, I believe that I'm,

830
00:41:16.202 --> 00:41:18.708
"I know I'm a part of something much bigger

831
00:41:18.708 --> 00:41:21.130
"than I can even imagine."

832
00:41:21.130 --> 00:41:22.473
<v Voiceover>When you come together,</v>

833
00:41:22.473 --> 00:41:25.492
is it for purpose, or is it really

834
00:41:25.492 --> 00:41:28.969
to go into a quiet space and see what reveals itself?

835
00:41:28.969 --> 00:41:30.484
<v ->Good question.</v>

836
00:41:30.484 --> 00:41:32.382
There's a lot of different types of circles.

837
00:41:32.382 --> 00:41:36.265
Usually when I'm introducing what women's circles are about

838
00:41:36.265 --> 00:41:40.350
I say there's sewing circles, and Bible study groups,

839
00:41:40.350 --> 00:41:43.251
and book groups and all of that,

840
00:41:43.251 --> 00:41:45.640
and they're done, conducted in a circle,

841
00:41:45.640 --> 00:41:47.592
and one person is speaking at a time,

842
00:41:47.592 --> 00:41:50.920
that's one of the principles of circling.

843
00:41:50.920 --> 00:41:53.938
So, there's a lot of different types,

844
00:41:53.938 --> 00:41:57.042
but what really drew me was to almost do

845
00:41:57.042 --> 00:41:59.719
like a prayer circle, in a way,

846
00:41:59.719 --> 00:42:02.876
just create a space, a sacred space,

847
00:42:02.876 --> 00:42:05.756
where women could be still for a moment,

848
00:42:05.756 --> 00:42:07.985
and be still with each other.

849
00:42:07.985 --> 00:42:09.606
Have a collective,

850
00:42:09.606 --> 00:42:12.529
that where two or more are gathered feeling

851
00:42:12.529 --> 00:42:15.153
and power happen.

852
00:42:15.153 --> 00:42:18.011
There's always a first feasting,

853
00:42:18.011 --> 00:42:19.729
and I think that's very important

854
00:42:19.729 --> 00:42:22.790
for women to be fed with each other,

855
00:42:22.790 --> 00:42:24.699
so I always feel like the circle kind of starts

856
00:42:24.699 --> 00:42:26.704
during that feasting time,

857
00:42:26.704 --> 00:42:29.541
and then the calling of the circle,

858
00:42:29.541 --> 00:42:32.698
which can be done with a beautiful tone,

859
00:42:32.698 --> 00:42:34.789
or just starting music.

860
00:42:34.789 --> 00:42:37.007
I use these Tibetan bells, and it's amazing

861
00:42:37.007 --> 00:42:39.749
how that seems to get everyone's attention

862
00:42:39.749 --> 00:42:41.327
and give them that sense of

863
00:42:41.327 --> 00:42:43.727
something really special's about to happen,

864
00:42:43.727 --> 00:42:45.626
and everyone gets quiet.

865
00:42:45.626 --> 00:42:46.884
Then, what I've been doing,

866
00:42:46.884 --> 00:42:49.369
what I call the sphere-circle formula,

867
00:42:49.369 --> 00:42:50.831
is exactly what I've been talking about:

868
00:42:50.831 --> 00:42:53.006
first the feasting, then the calling of the circle,

869
00:42:53.006 --> 00:42:57.657
and then, I create kind of a guided meditation,

870
00:42:57.657 --> 00:43:00.675
creating the actual container of the circle

871
00:43:00.675 --> 00:43:04.739
with a light that comes out of everyone's heart

872
00:43:04.739 --> 00:43:07.619
that streams around and connects everyone's arms.

873
00:43:07.619 --> 00:43:09.954
I don't really have people holding hands,

874
00:43:09.954 --> 00:43:13.357
it's more just having our hands placed out,

875
00:43:13.357 --> 00:43:16.621
and everyone who's experienced it really has,

876
00:43:16.621 --> 00:43:19.639
the feedback has been that they really feel that light

877
00:43:19.639 --> 00:43:23.597
coming around and that container being created.

878
00:43:23.597 --> 00:43:25.196
<v Voiceover>How many people do you normally</v>

879
00:43:25.196 --> 00:43:26.540
have in a circle?

880
00:43:26.540 --> 00:43:28.258
<v ->Well, it depends.</v>

881
00:43:28.258 --> 00:43:31.969
I have had for seven years an ongoing group

882
00:43:31.969 --> 00:43:34.551
of personal friends, select friends,

883
00:43:34.551 --> 00:43:37.590
which is really highly suggested in doing a circle,

884
00:43:37.590 --> 00:43:42.590
is to really be discerning about who you invite in

885
00:43:42.699 --> 00:43:45.696
because the safe space is very important,

886
00:43:45.696 --> 00:43:49.504
so I would say about 10 to 12 to 15

887
00:43:49.504 --> 00:43:51.125
was kind of the average.

888
00:43:51.125 --> 00:43:52.917
Then when I did my larger circle,

889
00:43:52.917 --> 00:43:54.560
because I found that there were so many women

890
00:43:54.560 --> 00:43:58.346
that wanted this and I wanted to provide that space

891
00:43:58.346 --> 00:44:01.898
so I did ongoing monthly circles that were open,

892
00:44:01.898 --> 00:44:05.087
but I still kind of screened people before they came in,

893
00:44:05.087 --> 00:44:08.010
and that would be up to, the largest circle

894
00:44:08.010 --> 00:44:10.495
was 48 women, but in general,

895
00:44:10.495 --> 00:44:12.863
it would be around 20, 20 women.

896
00:44:12.863 --> 00:44:17.342
The sharing, it's one of the important things

897
00:44:17.342 --> 00:44:19.924
in a circle is for each woman's voice

898
00:44:19.924 --> 00:44:21.566
to somehow be heard.

899
00:44:21.566 --> 00:44:24.745
With this beginning opening ritual that I created,

900
00:44:24.745 --> 00:44:28.414
I call it the candle lighting affirming ritual,

901
00:44:28.414 --> 00:44:31.603
each woman, one at a time, lights a candle saying,

902
00:44:31.603 --> 00:44:35.219
"I am the," and then you use some kind of adjective

903
00:44:35.219 --> 00:44:38.451
to describe who you are, such as prosperous,

904
00:44:38.451 --> 00:44:43.325
succulent, calm, confident, free-flowing Deborah,

905
00:44:43.325 --> 00:44:46.066
and then the whole circle will say,

906
00:44:46.066 --> 00:44:48.114
"We hold that for you, Deborah."

907
00:44:48.114 --> 00:44:50.855
And then the next woman lights her candle off of me,

908
00:44:50.855 --> 00:44:53.362
and it goes around, and there's just,

909
00:44:53.362 --> 00:44:55.409
some women start crying because of

910
00:44:55.409 --> 00:44:58.897
the moving experience of just holding light

911
00:44:58.897 --> 00:45:02.748
and being listened to and being able to say the, "I am."

912
00:45:02.748 --> 00:45:06.022
It's very powerful, and to have that held for you

913
00:45:06.022 --> 00:45:08.860
with all these open hearts.

914
00:45:08.860 --> 00:45:12.155
<v Voiceover>Your circles no longer contain just women.</v>

915
00:45:12.155 --> 00:45:13.339
Is that correct?

916
00:45:13.339 --> 00:45:14.267
I mean, you have your girlfriends,

917
00:45:14.267 --> 00:45:16.379
but aren't you expanding the circles

918
00:45:16.379 --> 00:45:20.624
to include men, which I think is really essential.

919
00:45:20.624 --> 00:45:25.019
<v ->Yes, I've found that this formula works for all people,</v>

920
00:45:25.019 --> 00:45:28.293
and the circle principles are important for

921
00:45:28.293 --> 00:45:30.362
all people to experience.

922
00:45:30.362 --> 00:45:35.023
The idea of being heard and being in sacred space,

923
00:45:35.023 --> 00:45:39.364
and having non-judgement, especially of yourself,

924
00:45:39.364 --> 00:45:42.831
and the speaking one at a time,

925
00:45:42.831 --> 00:45:47.831
and feeling like whatever you're saying in the circle

926
00:45:48.185 --> 00:45:50.585
is going to stay in the circle.

927
00:45:50.585 --> 00:45:52.558
These are all really important principles

928
00:45:52.558 --> 00:45:54.574
that men are craving, too.

929
00:45:54.574 --> 00:45:56.921
So, I have, I think it's important for women

930
00:45:56.921 --> 00:46:00.216
to still gather solely as women,

931
00:46:00.216 --> 00:46:03.533
however, especially now, expanding into

932
00:46:03.533 --> 00:46:06.371
the inclusion of men and letting them

933
00:46:06.371 --> 00:46:09.197
express their more feminine side,

934
00:46:09.197 --> 00:46:12.898
and encourage that in the sharing of the heart.

935
00:46:12.898 --> 00:46:14.103
<v Voiceover>And encourage the principles</v>

936
00:46:14.103 --> 00:46:16.493
that are classically identified as feminine,

937
00:46:16.493 --> 00:46:18.999
such as nurturing and compassion and caring,

938
00:46:18.999 --> 00:46:21.602
and finding consensus and so forth,

939
00:46:21.602 --> 00:46:24.183
those are the essential elements that are needed

940
00:46:24.183 --> 00:46:28.684
to heal the state we're in politically, ecologically, etc.

941
00:46:28.684 --> 00:46:32.492
It does seem logical that men and women come together

942
00:46:32.492 --> 00:46:35.435
because it is about interconnectedness of all, isn't it?

943
00:46:35.435 --> 00:46:36.417
<v ->Very much.</v>

944
00:46:36.417 --> 00:46:39.339
That's one of my monikers for my magazine,

945
00:46:39.339 --> 00:46:42.720
Spheres Circles Publication is, it's all about connecting

946
00:46:42.720 --> 00:46:45.920
for the benefit of all, and I truly believe,

947
00:46:45.920 --> 00:46:48.683
and there's been a lot of scientific proof of,

948
00:46:48.683 --> 00:46:50.357
when people come together,

949
00:46:50.357 --> 00:46:55.050
then sending out an energy that is of a positive nature,

950
00:46:55.050 --> 00:46:57.322
and when we come together in circles,

951
00:46:57.322 --> 00:47:00.202
what I've phrased happens is

952
00:47:00.202 --> 00:47:02.708
we create, like pockets of peace,

953
00:47:02.708 --> 00:47:04.660
whether it's just with a single girlfriend

954
00:47:04.660 --> 00:47:08.116
or if you're sitting around a dinner table.

955
00:47:08.116 --> 00:47:10.815
You'll notice the energy shift if it goes from

956
00:47:10.815 --> 00:47:13.780
people just blabbing and having separate conversations

957
00:47:13.780 --> 00:47:17.033
to all of a sudden, bringing it into a single conversation

958
00:47:17.033 --> 00:47:19.475
where one person is speaking at a time.

959
00:47:19.475 --> 00:47:22.046
All of a sudden, there is a sense of sacredness

960
00:47:22.046 --> 00:47:24.904
that is there and people feel like they

961
00:47:24.904 --> 00:47:27.155
don't want to leave that space.

962
00:47:27.155 --> 00:47:29.182
<v Voiceover>We really,</v>

963
00:47:30.252 --> 00:47:32.765
bringing women together so we can express ourselves

964
00:47:32.765 --> 00:47:36.829
and our frustrations even at times,

965
00:47:36.829 --> 00:47:40.359
really, the time for getting together and just bitching

966
00:47:40.359 --> 00:47:43.634
is past, this is not something that's really

967
00:47:43.634 --> 00:47:46.204
valuable or needed any more in that sense.

968
00:47:46.204 --> 00:47:48.305
To express how you feel honestly,

969
00:47:48.305 --> 00:47:51.804
but in a much more open context toward healing,

970
00:47:51.804 --> 00:47:54.940
and openness and understanding rather than

971
00:47:54.940 --> 00:47:58.011
coming together with your girlfriends and complaining;

972
00:47:58.011 --> 00:48:00.678
complaining about your husband, this sort of thing,

973
00:48:00.678 --> 00:48:01.979
or your kids--

974
00:48:01.979 --> 00:48:04.326
<v ->And that's where creating that sacred space</v>

975
00:48:04.326 --> 00:48:06.640
feeling in a circle is so important

976
00:48:06.640 --> 00:48:09.317
because it's almost like you would feel strange

977
00:48:09.317 --> 00:48:12.261
talking in that way in that particular space

978
00:48:12.261 --> 00:48:14.192
when it's created properly.

979
00:48:14.192 --> 00:48:15.216
<v Voiceover>Very true.</v>

980
00:48:15.216 --> 00:48:17.925
Really important to do this; very important at this time,

981
00:48:17.925 --> 00:48:20.719
as both you and Jean have discussed.

982
00:48:20.719 --> 00:48:23.311
How do you go about starting a circle?

983
00:48:23.311 --> 00:48:26.052
<v ->Well, the first thing you want to do is</v>

984
00:48:26.052 --> 00:48:29.188
decide who you would want to share that space with.

985
00:48:29.188 --> 00:48:31.193
That's very important.

986
00:48:31.193 --> 00:48:35.748
So just putting out the word and setting the guidelines for,

987
00:48:35.748 --> 00:48:38.510
I always have on every invitation,

988
00:48:38.510 --> 00:48:41.337
whether it's for an event or for the women that have been

989
00:48:41.337 --> 00:48:43.395
coming for seven years, a reminder of what

990
00:48:43.395 --> 00:48:45.464
the guidelines of the circle are,

991
00:48:45.464 --> 00:48:48.707
and really honoring coming on time,

992
00:48:48.707 --> 00:48:50.893
and not getting up and leaving,

993
00:48:50.893 --> 00:48:53.795
and really committing to being present

994
00:48:53.795 --> 00:48:56.738
for that block of time.

995
00:48:56.738 --> 00:48:59.202
The first circle I ever experienced

996
00:48:59.202 --> 00:49:01.410
had been together for nine years,

997
00:49:01.410 --> 00:49:03.959
and these women let no one else in that circle,

998
00:49:03.959 --> 00:49:08.706
and they did not even begin speaking until they felt like it

999
00:49:08.706 --> 00:49:11.372
and I was invited in, and I remember that night

1000
00:49:11.372 --> 00:49:14.625
sitting there and there was, like this long pause,

1001
00:49:14.625 --> 00:49:16.406
and I was tired to begin with, and I thought,

1002
00:49:16.406 --> 00:49:18.636
"Oh my god, this is going to be a long night."

1003
00:49:18.636 --> 00:49:20.865
Finally, I just relaxed into it,

1004
00:49:20.865 --> 00:49:22.913
and all of a sudden a woman lit a candle,

1005
00:49:22.913 --> 00:49:24.630
and she just started talking,

1006
00:49:24.630 --> 00:49:27.435
and sometimes she was crying, and sometimes she was laughing

1007
00:49:27.435 --> 00:49:29.686
and I found myself with tears

1008
00:49:29.686 --> 00:49:31.456
streaming down my face with her

1009
00:49:31.456 --> 00:49:34.123
and I found myself laughing with her,

1010
00:49:34.123 --> 00:49:36.331
and all of a sudden, I got that feeling

1011
00:49:36.331 --> 00:49:39.861
of the golden thread that connects us all

1012
00:49:39.861 --> 00:49:43.829
and a sense of being each of these women,

1013
00:49:43.829 --> 00:49:46.197
and I felt energized by that.

1014
00:49:46.197 --> 00:49:49.546
It's really important, one of the things

1015
00:49:49.546 --> 00:49:51.498
I learned about that particular circle

1016
00:49:51.498 --> 00:49:54.004
was the benefit of being with women

1017
00:49:54.004 --> 00:49:57.599
that you felt so safe with, and that you could share with.

1018
00:49:57.599 --> 00:50:00.692
I've been doing these open circles strictly so that

1019
00:50:00.692 --> 00:50:03.774
people could experience this particular formula

1020
00:50:03.774 --> 00:50:06.611
and see how easy it is to start your own circle

1021
00:50:06.611 --> 00:50:09.001
and hopefully encourage other circles,

1022
00:50:09.001 --> 00:50:12.339
and also to provide that space on a regular basis

1023
00:50:12.339 --> 00:50:14.366
that women knew would just be there.

1024
00:50:14.366 --> 00:50:17.192
Jean always, and The Millionth Circle

1025
00:50:17.192 --> 00:50:19.656
and their guidance on creating circles

1026
00:50:19.656 --> 00:50:23.976
always suggests never having a single facilitator in circle

1027
00:50:23.976 --> 00:50:26.482
because the idea of the circle is,

1028
00:50:26.482 --> 00:50:29.106
there is no leader, no head.

1029
00:50:29.106 --> 00:50:31.612
But what I've found in Los Angeles

1030
00:50:31.612 --> 00:50:33.682
was that the women, especially the ones

1031
00:50:33.682 --> 00:50:36.469
that had to lead all the time for their work

1032
00:50:36.469 --> 00:50:38.249
or in their organizations,

1033
00:50:38.249 --> 00:50:40.783
were so happy to come and be able to just

1034
00:50:40.783 --> 00:50:44.036
kick back and know that things would be taken care of.

1035
00:50:44.036 --> 00:50:49.036
Yes, how it is important for whoever is facilitating

1036
00:50:49.774 --> 00:50:54.734
to let their egos behind because the idea of the circle

1037
00:50:54.734 --> 00:50:59.734
and being in the circumference of a circle container

1038
00:51:00.728 --> 00:51:05.400
is that there is no leader, and there is no intimidation.

1039
00:51:05.400 --> 00:51:08.600
It's really important to have a certain type of temperament

1040
00:51:08.600 --> 00:51:13.314
if you are going to be strictly the facilitator for a circle

1041
00:51:13.314 --> 00:51:16.098
or if you're just doing it for an evening.

1042
00:51:16.098 --> 00:51:18.903
There's certain guidelines for facilitating circles

1043
00:51:18.903 --> 00:51:20.599
that are very important.

1044
00:51:20.599 --> 00:51:21.676
<v Voiceover>I would think you would have to be</v>

1045
00:51:21.676 --> 00:51:26.082
fairly confident in your ability to hold energy and give

1046
00:51:26.082 --> 00:51:28.801
a little bit of instruction or guidance anyway, right?

1047
00:51:28.801 --> 00:51:30.540
<v ->Yeah, to be sensitive to what's happening</v>

1048
00:51:30.540 --> 00:51:32.257
with the energy of the circle.

1049
00:51:32.257 --> 00:51:34.977
Sometimes, someone does go into story

1050
00:51:34.977 --> 00:51:37.921
and you find that it's very important that,

1051
00:51:37.921 --> 00:51:41.291
for everyone, that it is completed,

1052
00:51:41.291 --> 00:51:43.819
and you don't want to interrupt that.

1053
00:51:43.819 --> 00:51:48.213
Or if a woman's crying, in circle,

1054
00:51:48.213 --> 00:51:50.859
it's very important for the women

1055
00:51:50.859 --> 00:51:55.859
to be guided not to hold back their nurturing quality

1056
00:51:56.149 --> 00:51:58.538
of wanting to immediately pull out a Kleenex

1057
00:51:58.538 --> 00:52:00.607
and hand it to the woman.

1058
00:52:00.607 --> 00:52:04.650
You want to allow someone to feel safe

1059
00:52:04.650 --> 00:52:07.594
to let, you know, whatever's coming out come out.

1060
00:52:07.594 --> 00:52:09.172
<v Voiceover>To complete itself.</v>

1061
00:52:09.172 --> 00:52:11.007
So really, it's quite simple.

1062
00:52:11.007 --> 00:52:13.567
It's a matter of desire and intention

1063
00:52:13.567 --> 00:52:15.956
and creating the space.

1064
00:52:15.956 --> 00:52:18.004
<v ->Yes, and the important word, too,</v>

1065
00:52:18.004 --> 00:52:19.881
we find is willingness.

1066
00:52:19.881 --> 00:52:22.067
The willingness to show up.

1067
00:52:22.067 --> 00:52:24.201
<v Voiceover>And you have a wonderful publication</v>

1068
00:52:24.201 --> 00:52:26.408
that you've created in support to all of this

1069
00:52:26.408 --> 00:52:29.608
and, really, to augment your endeavors called Spheres?

1070
00:52:29.608 --> 00:52:31.955
<v ->Yes, Spheres Circles, it started out as</v>

1071
00:52:31.955 --> 00:52:33.971
<v ->[Voiceover and Deborah] Spheres Women's Circles,</v>

1072
00:52:33.971 --> 00:52:37.597
<v ->Which, my website is still sphereswomenscircles.com.</v>

1073
00:52:37.597 --> 00:52:42.450
However, I found after doing the magazine for five years

1074
00:52:42.450 --> 00:52:45.629
that it felt very important to include men,

1075
00:52:45.629 --> 00:52:49.319
so it's become a one of a kind yin yang style magazine,

1076
00:52:49.319 --> 00:52:51.602
in which you flip over the cover and it's men,

1077
00:52:51.602 --> 00:52:54.567
and my husband is actually involved now, and that's been--

1078
00:52:54.567 --> 00:52:55.985
<v Voiceover>Oh, and he writes beautifully.</v>

1079
00:52:55.985 --> 00:52:57.148
<v ->Very symbolic thing.</v>

1080
00:52:57.148 --> 00:52:58.908
<v Voiceover>Yes, it is, it's a wonderful publication,</v>

1081
00:52:58.908 --> 00:53:00.913
and I'd encourage anybody watching,

1082
00:53:00.913 --> 00:53:04.134
they can get a copy of it through your website

1083
00:53:04.134 --> 00:53:06.555
or subscribe to it, right?

1084
00:53:06.555 --> 00:53:08.731
<v ->Yes, they can request a complimentary issue,</v>

1085
00:53:08.731 --> 00:53:10.448
and, or subscribe.

1086
00:53:10.448 --> 00:53:13.819
Well, what I have always said was how

1087
00:53:13.819 --> 00:53:18.010
being in circle has really helped me be

1088
00:53:19.710 --> 00:53:23.098
accepting of my own femininity,

1089
00:53:23.098 --> 00:53:26.554
and that was a tough thing growing up

1090
00:53:26.554 --> 00:53:28.943
in the times that we all did,

1091
00:53:28.943 --> 00:53:32.730
many of us women, with bringing out our masculine

1092
00:53:32.730 --> 00:53:35.908
more and more, and trying to be the super woman,

1093
00:53:35.908 --> 00:53:37.348
and handling it all.

1094
00:53:37.348 --> 00:53:39.396
So to just honor more and more

1095
00:53:39.396 --> 00:53:43.022
the feminine qualities of the nurturing,

1096
00:53:43.022 --> 00:53:47.171
of the listening, of the being a container and holding space

1097
00:53:47.171 --> 00:53:49.955
and how important that is to bring that

1098
00:53:49.955 --> 00:53:52.253
into all aspects of our lives.

